  <data name="About_WhatTitle"        xml:space="preserve"><value>What is OpenSource2Roblox?</value></data>
  <data name="About_WhatBody1"        xml:space="preserve"><value>OpenSource2Roblox is a free, open-source desktop application that converts Source Engine game content into Roblox-compatible place files and assets. It reads BSP map files, MDL models, and VTF textures from games like CS:GO, Half-Life 2, Team Fortress 2, and Portal, then exports them directly into Roblox Studio.</value></data>
  <data name="About_WhatBody2"        xml:space="preserve"><value>Textures are automatically extracted and placed in Roblox Studio's content directory so they load seamlessly when you open the exported place file. Static props, entity lights, displacement terrain, and ropes are all supported.</value></data>
